M-1 : Reversing Digit by Digit
This idea for this approach is to repeatedly extract the last digit of n using the modulus operator (n % 10) and appending it to the reverse number (revNum). 
After extracting the digit, the number n is reduced by dividing it by 10 (n = n / 10). 
This process continues until n becomes 0. 
Finally, the reversed number (revNum) is returned.

class GfG {
    static int reverseDigits(int n) {
        int revNum = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            revNum = revNum * 10 + n % 10;
            n = n / 10;
        }
        return revNum;
    }
}
